snippet.textDisplay:
I saw this opening weekend in theatres. It was the most charged audience I've ever been with. Hell, even the previews were great. There was one for a movie that looked interesting and you could hear everyone whispering about going to see it "directed by N.Night" Entire theater groans out loud, then laughs at everyone groaning. There was laughter, cheering, just so much energy that even if the movie had sucked it would have been the best movie ever.
Instead it's hands down my favourite movie ever. Hell, it has 4 commentary tracks and I've listened to them all and found them all interesting. So many small details that you're unlikely to notice but SOMEONE has. Stuff like the CN tower behind the backdrop, the heart lens flares on the bus, the ninja and scott standing in the same position during the nega-ninja bit and so much more.

snippet.textDisplay: What's wrong with a movie depicting a guy stalking someone, or when Todd strikes a girl? The movie isn't trying to say 'these things are okay'. One's a deeply flawed protagonist caught in the grip of obsession, and the other is explicitly stated to be an evil ex. And it wouldn't matter either way, because they're characters in a movie. I know Cinemasins says a lot of things with irony, but if there's irony here, I can't detect it.
snippet.textOriginal: What's wrong with a movie depicting a guy stalking someone, or when Todd strikes a girl? The movie isn't trying to say 'these things are okay'. One's a deeply flawed protagonist caught in the grip of obsession, and the other is explicitly stated to be an _evil_ ex. And it wouldn't matter either way, because *they're characters in a movie.*  I know Cinemasins says a lot of things with irony, but if there's irony here, I can't detect it.
